  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6781.76 sitting just above the 6777 GEX flip in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net long gamma and providing stabilizing flows. The massive positive gamma wall at 6800 (+62.9B) creates a natural ceiling where dealers will aggressively sell into any rally attempts, while the negative gamma pocket at 6765 (-8.9B) should trigger dealer buying if we break lower. Given the -6.7% 1-min move and thick gamma walls stacked from 6780-6800, expect dealers to fade this recent weakness and provide buying support around current levels.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect price to stabilize and chop between 6770-6795 with dealers capping upside near 6800.",
